name: sendKeys
description: Simulates keystroke events on the specified element, as though you typed the value key-by-key. This simulates a real user typing every character in the specified string; it is also bound by the limitations of a real user, like not being able to type into a invisible or read only elements. This is useful for dynamic UI widgets (like auto-completing combo boxes) that require explicit key events. Unlike the simple 'type' command, which forces the specified value into the page directly, this command will not replace the existing content.
